						<summary>

						<p>Slab built into the ground near a well in a field.</p>						

						<p>1390 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This worn out record is dated <hi rend="bold">Śaka 1311, Śukla, Mīna 3, Sunday</hi> corresponding to <hi rend="bold">1390 A.D., February 26</hi> when the week-day was Saturday.</p>						

						<p>It seems to register gifts of land probably to god Mañjanāthadēva.</p>						

						</summary>
